op 100 Japanese Mystery Novels of All Time]]: ''The Devotion of Suspect X''\n* 2012 \u2013 Ranked as the No. 18 novel on the [[Tozai Mystery Best 100|Top 100 Japanese Mystery Novels of All Time]]: ''Journey under the Midnight Sun''\n*2018 - Ranked as No. 1 novel on the Weekly [[Bungeishunj\u016b]] Mystery Best 10: ''Chinmoku no Par\u0113do'' (\u6c88\u9ed9\u306e\u30d1\u30ec\u30fc\u30c9, ''Silent Parade'')\n\n==Bibliography==\nBy 2018 Higashino had published 66 novels, 20 short story collections, and one picture book. In all, there were 715 works in 8 languages by Higashino worldwide in 2020, excluding 20 which were about him.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n===[[Manabu Yukawa|Detective Galileo]] series===\n*Novels\n**{{nihongo|''Y\u014dgisha X no Kenshin''|\u5bb9\u7591\u8005X\u306e\u732e\u8eab|}}, 2005 (''[[The Devotion of Suspect X]]'', [[St. Martin's Press|Minotaur Books]], 2011)\n**{{nihongo|''Seijo no Ky\u016bsai''|\u8056\u5973\u306e\u6551\u6e08|}}, 2008 (''[[Salvation of a Saint]]'', Minotaur Books, 2012)\n**{{nihongo|''Manatsu no H\u014dteishiki''|\u771f\u590f\u306e\u65b9\u7a0b\u5f0f|}}, 2011 (''A Midsummer's Equation'', Minotaur Books, 2016)\n**{{nihongo|''Chinmoku no Par\u0113do''|\u6c88\u9ed9\u306e\u30d1\u30ec\u30fc\u30c9|}}, 2018 (''Silent Parade'')\n*Short story collections\n**{{nihongo|''Tantei Galileo''|\u63a2\u5075\u30ac\u30ea\u30ec\u30aa|}}, 1998 (''Detective Galileo'')\n**{{nihongo|''Yochimu''|\u4e88\u77e5\u5922|}}, 2000 (''Foresight Dream'')\n**{{nihongo|''Galileo no Kun\u014d''|\u30ac\u30ea\u30ec\u30aa\u306e\u82e6\u60a9|}}, 2008 (''The Anguish of Galileo'')\n**{{nihongo|''Kyoz\u014d no D\u014dkeshi''|\u865a\u50cf\u306e\u9053\u5316\u5e2b|}}, 2012 (''The Virtual Clown'')\n**{{nihongo|''Kindan no Majutsu''|\u7981\u65ad\u306e\u9b54\u8853|}}, 2012 (''The Forbidden Magic'')\n\n===Police Detective Kaga series===\n*Novels\n**{{nihongo|''Sotsugy\u014d''|\u5352\u696d|}}, 1986 (''Graduation'')\n**{{nihongo|''Nemuri no mori''|\u7761\u308a\u306e\u68ee|}}, 1989 (''The Forest in Sleep'')\n**{{nihongo|''Dochiraka ga Kanojo o Koroshita''|\u3069\u3061\u3089\u304b\u304c\u5f7c\u5973\u3092\u6bba\u3057\u305f|}}, 1996 (''Who Killed Her'')\n**{{nihongo|''Akui''|\u60aa\u610f|}}, 1996 (''Malice'', Minotaur Books, 2014)\n**{{nihongo|''Watashi ga Kare o Koroshita''|\u79c1\u304c\u5f7c\u3092\u6bba\u3057\u305f|}}, 1999 (''I Killed Him'')\n**{{nihongo|''Akai Yubi''|\u8d64\u3044\u6307|}}, 2006 (''The Red Finger'')\n**{{nihongo|''Shinzanmono''|\u65b0\u53c2\u8005|}}, 2009 (''Newcomer'', Minotaur Books, 2017)\n**{{nihongo|''Kirin no Tsubasa''|\u9e92\u9e9f\u306e\u7ffc|}}, 2011 (''Beautiful Wings'')\n**{{nihongo|''Inori no Maku ga Oriru Toki''|\u7948\u308a\u306e\u5e55\u304c\u4e0b\u308a\u308b\u6642|}}, 2013 (''When the Curtain of Prayer Descends'')\n*Short story collection\n**{{nihongo|''Uso o M\u014d Hitotsu Dake''|\u5618\u3092\u3082\u3046\u3072\u3068\u3064\u3060\u3051|}}, 2000 (''Just One More Lie'')\n\n===Naniwa Detective Boys series===\n*{{nihongo|''[[Osaka|Naniwa]] Sh\u014dnen Tanteidan''|\u6d6a\u82b1\u5c11\u5e74\u63a2\u5075\u56e3|}}, 1988, Short story collection (''Naniwa Detective Boys'')\n*{{nihongo|''Shinobu Sense ni Sayonara''|\u3057\u306e\u3076\u30bb\u30f3\u30bb\u306b\u30b5\u30e8\u30ca\u30e9|}}, 1993, Short story collection (''Goodbye, Miss Shinobu'')\n\n===Detective Daigoro Tenkaichi series===\n*{{nihongo|''Meitantei no Okite''|\u540d\u63a2\u5075\u306e\u639f|}}, 1996, Short story collection (''The Rule of the Detective'')\n*{{nihongo|''Meitantei no Jubaku''|\u540d\u63a2\u5075\u306e\u546a\u7e1b|}}, 1996, Novel (''The Curse of the Detective'')\n\n===Other novels===\n*{{nihongo|''H\u014dkago''|\u653e\u8ab2\u5f8c|}}, 1985 (''After School'')\n*{{nihongo|''Hakuba Sans\u014d Satsujin Jiken''|\u767d\u99ac\u5c71\u8358\u6bba\u4eba\u4e8b\u4ef6|}}, 1986 (''The Murder in Mansion Hakuba'')\n*{{nihongo|''Gakusei-gai no Satsujin''|\u5b66\u751f\u8857\u306e\u6bba\u4eba|}}, 1987 (''The Murder in the College Town'')\n*{{nihongo|''J\u016bichi Moji no Satsujin''|11\u6587\u5b57\u306e\u6bba\u4eba|}}, 1987 (''The Case of 11 Letters'')\n*{{nihongo|''Maky\u016b''|\u9b54\u7403|}}, 1988 (''Magic Ball'')\n*{{nihongo|''Uinku de Kampai''|\u30a6\u30a4\u30f3\u30af\u3067\u4e7e\u676f|}}, 1988 (''Cheers with a Wink'')\n*{{nihongo|''J\u016bji Yashiki no Piero''|\u5341\u5b57\u5c4b\u6577\u306e\u30d4\u30a8\u30ed|}}, 1989 (''The Clown of House Juji'')\n*{{nihongo|''Ch\u014djin Keikaku''|\u9ce5\u4eba\u8a08\u753b|}}, 1989 (''Plan Chojin'')\n*{{nihongo|''Satsujin Genba wa Kumo no Ue''|\u6bba\u4eba\u73fe\u5834\u306f\u96f2\u306e\u4e0a|}}, 1989 (''Murder on the Cloud'')\n*{{nihongo|''Bur\u016btasu no Shinz\u014d''|\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30bf\u30b9\u306e\u5fc3\u81d3|}}, 1989 (''Heart of Burutasu'')\n*{{nihongo|''Shukumei''|\u5bbf\u547d|}}, 1990 (''Fate'')\n*{{nihongo|''Kamen Sans\u014d Satsujin Jiken''|\u4eee\u9762\u5c71\u8358\u6bba\u4eba\u4e8b\u4ef6|}}, 1990 (''The Murder in Mansion Masquerade'')\n*{{nihongo|''Henshin''|\u5909\u8eab|}}, 1991 (''Transformation'')\n*{{nihongo|''Kair\u014dtei Satsujin Jiken''|\u56de\u5eca\u4ead\u6bba\u4eba\u4e8b\u4ef6|}}, 1991 (''The Murder in Kairotei'')\n*{{nihongo|''Aru Tozasareta Yuki no Sans\u014d de''|\u3042\u308b\u9589\u3056\u3055\u308c\u305f\u96ea\u306e\u5c71\u8358\u3067|}}, 1992 (''In a Mansion Covered with Snow'')\n*{{nihongo|''Utsukushiki Ky\u014dki''|\u7f8e\u3057\u304d\u51f6\u5668|}}, 1992 (''Beautiful Weapon'')\n*{{nihongo|''D\u014dky\u016bsei''|\u540c\u7d1a\u751f|}}, 1993 (''Classmate'')\n*{{nihongo|''Bunshin''|\u5206\u8eab|}}, 1993 (''Alter Ego'')\n*{{nihongo|''Mukashi Boku ga Shinda Ie''|\u3080\u304b\u3057\u50d5\u304c\u6b7b\u3093\u3060\u5bb6|}}, 1994 (''The Home Where I Died'')\n*{{nihongo|''Niji o Ayatsuru Sh\u014dnen''|\u8679\u3092\u64cd\u308b\u5c11\u5e74|}}, 1994 (''The Boy Who Controlled the Rainbow'')\n*{{nihongo|''Parareru W\u0101rudo Rabu Sut\u014dr\u012b (Parallel world love story)''|\u30d1\u30e9\u30ec\u30eb\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9\u30fb\u30e9\u30d6\u30b9\u30c8\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc|}}, 1995\n*{{nihongo|''T