|09}}\n| 2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|16}}\n| 2*\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Toosie Slide]]\"\n| align=\"left\"|Drake\n| 2\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|16}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 2*\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Death Bed]]\"\n| align=\"left\"|[[Powfu]] <small>featuring [[Beabadoobee]]</small>\n| 7\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|23}}\n| 1\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|23}}\n| 1*\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Blueberry Faygo]]\"\n| align=\"left\"|[[Lil Mosey]]\n| 9\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|23}}\n| 1\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|30}}\n| 1*\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[You'll Never Walk Alone]]\"\n| align=\"left\"|[[Michael Ball]], [[Tom Moore (fundraiser)|Captain Tom Moore]] & The Voices of Care Choir\n| 1\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|04|30}}\n| 1\n|-\n|}\n\n==Entries by artist==\n[[File:SAINt JHN 2018.jpg|thumb|right|150px|alt=|Guyanese-American rapper [[Saint Jhn]] reached number-one in March this year thanks a remix of his 2016 song \"[[Roses (Saint Jhn song)|Roses]]\" by Kazakh DJ [[Imanbek]].]]\n[[File:Billie Eilish at Pukkelpop Festival - 18 AUGUST 2019 (01) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|150px|alt=|American singer [[Billie Eilish]] became the first artist born in the 21st century to score a UK number-one single when \"[[No Time to Die (song)|No Time to Die]]\", the theme tune from ''[[No Time to Die|the James Bond movie of the same name]]'', topped the chart in February this year. \"No Time to Die\" also became only the second James Bond theme tune to reach the top of the British charts.]]\n{{see also|List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2020s#2020}}\nThe following table shows artists who have achieved two or more top 10 entries in 2020, including singles that reached their peak in 2019. The figures include both main artists and featured artists, while appearances on ensemble charity records are also counted for each artist. The total number of weeks an artist spent in the top ten in 2020 is also shown.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:55px;\" data-sort-type=\"number\"| Entries\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Artist\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:55px;\"| Country of origin\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:55px;\" data-sort-type=\"number\"| Weeks\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:300px;\"| Singles\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center\" | 3\n|[[Dua Lipa]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:enter\" | {{UK}}\n|16*\n| \"[[Don't Start Now (Dua Lipa song)|Don't Start Now]]\", \"[[Physical (Dua Lipa song)|Physical]]\", \"[[Break My Heart (Dua Lipa song)|Break My Heart]]\"\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center\" | 2\n|[[George Michael]] {{ref label|George|K|k}}{{ref label|George|L|l}}\n|1\n| \"[[Last Christmas]]\", \"[[Do They Know It's Christmas?]]\"\n|-\n|[[Lewis Capaldi]]\n|{{SCO}}\n|11\n| \"[[Before You Go (Lewis Capaldi song)|Before You Go]]\", \"[[Someone You Loved]]\"\n|-\n|[[Billie Eilish]]\n|{{USA}}\n|8\n|\"[[Everything I Wanted]]\", \"[[No Time to Die (song)|No Time to Die]]\"\n|-\n|[[Justin Bieber]]\n|{{CAN}}\n|8\n| \"[[Yummy (Justin Bieber song)|Yummy]]\", \"[[Intentions (Justin Bieber song)|Intentions]]\"\n|-\n|[[Aitch (rapper)|Aitch]]\n|{{UK}}\n|4\n| \"Ei8ht Mile\", \"Rain\"\n|-\n|[[Drake (rapper)|Drake]]\n|{{CAN}}\n|9*\n| \"[[Life Is Good (song)|Life is Good]]\", \"[[Toosie Slide]]\"\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{refbegin|2}}\n*{{note label|Someone|A|a}} \"Someone You Loved\" re-entered the top 10 at number 10 on 11 June 2019 (week ending).\n*{{note label|All I Want|B|b}} \"All I Want for Christmas\" re-entered the top 10 on 12 December 2019 (week ending), having originally peaked at number 2 upon release in 1994.\n*{{note label|River|C|c}} \"River\" re-entered the top 10 at number 1 on 2 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Last Christmas|D|d}} \"Last Christmas\" re-entered the top 10 on 19 December 2019 (week ending), having originally peaked at number 2 upon release in 1984.\n*{{note label|Fairytale of New York|E|e}} \"Fairytale of New York\" re-entered the top 10 on 2 January 2020 (week ending), having originally peaked at number 2 upon release in 1987.\n*{{note label|Merry Christmas Everyone|F|f}} \"Merry Christmas Everyone\" re-entered the top 10 on 2 January 2020 (week ending), having originally peaked at number 1 upon release in 1985.\n*{{note label|Band Aid|G|g}} Released as a charity single by Band Aid in 1984 to aid [[1983\u20131985 famine in Ethiopia|famine relief]] in [[Ethiopia]].\n*{{note label|Do They Know It's Christmas|H|h}} \"Do They Know It's Christmas?\" re-entered the top 10 on 2 January 2020 (week ending), having originally peaked at number 1 upon release in 1984.\n*{{note label|Elton John|I|i}} \"Step into Christmas\" re-entered the top 10 at its new peak of number 8 on 2 January 2020 (week ending). It originally peaked at number 24 on its initial release in 1973. It reached the top 10 for the first time on 3 January 2019 (week ending), originally peaking at number 10.\n*{{note label|Wizzard|J|j}} \"I Wish It Could Be Christmas Everyday\" re-entered the top 10 on 2 January 2020 (week ending), having originally peaked at number 4 upon release in 1973.\n*{{note label|George|K|k}} Figure includes a top-ten hit as a member of the group Wham!\n*{{note label|George|L|l}} Figure includes an appearance on the \"Do They Know It's Christmas?\" charity single by Band Aid.\n*{{note label|Dance|M|m}} \"Dance Monkey\" re-entered the top 10 at number 5 on 9 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Lose|N|n}} \"Lose You to Love Me\" re-entered the top 10 at number 10 on 9 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Don't|O|o}} \"Don't Start Now\" re-entered the top 10 at number 3 on 9 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Everything I Wanted|P|p}} \"Everything I Wanted\" re-entered the top 10 at number 6 on 9 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Roxanne|Q|q}} \"Roxanne\" re-entered the top 10 at number 4 on 9 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Before You Go|R|r}} \"Before You Go\" re-entered the top 10 at number 2 on 9 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Someone|S|s}} \"Someone You Loved\" re-entered the top 10 at number 7 on 16 January 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Everything|T|t}} \"Everything I Wanted\" re-entered the top 10 at number 8 on 6 February 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Adore You|U|u}} \"Adore You\" re-entered the top 10 at number 10 on 13 February 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Adore You|V|v}} \"Adore You\" re-entered the top 10 at number 10 on 5 March 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Godzilla|W|w}} \"Godzilla\" re-entered the top 10 at number 9 on 26 March 2020 (week ending).\n*{{note label|Intentions|X|x}} \"Intentions\" re-entered the top 10 at number 10 on 26 March 2020 (week ending).\n{{refend|2}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[2020 in British music]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2020s|List of number-one singles from the 2020s (UK)]]\n\n==References==\n'''General'''\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart-singles/ |title=Six decades of singles charts |publisher=The Official Charts Company |accessdate=23 April 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110303221018/http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart-singles/ |archivedate=3 March 2011}}\n\n'''Specific'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20191226/7501/ 2020 singles chart archive] at the [[Official Charts Company]] (click on relevant week)\n{{UKTop10s}}\n{{UK Music Charts}}\n\n[[Category:2020 record charts|United Kingdom top 10 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 in British music|Top 10 singles]]\n[[Category:Lists of UK top-ten singles|2020]]\n", "text_old": "{{2020s in music (UK)}}\n[[File:FEQ July 2018 The Weeknd (44778856382) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|200px|alt=|Canadian singer [[The Weeknd]] achieved his first ever UK number-one single in February 2020 with \"[[Blinding Lights]]\", his eighth top 10 entry in the United Kingdom. So far, the song has spent eight non-consecutive weeks at number-one and 15 weeks in the top 10 altogether.]]\nThe [[UK Singles Chart]] is one of many music charts compiled by the [[Official Charts Company]] that calculates the best-selling singles of the week in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/|title=The Official Charts Company|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=28 December 2014}}</ref> Since 2004 the chart has been based on the sales of both [[CD single|physical singles]] and [[music download|digital downloads]], with [[airplay]] figures excluded from the official chart.<ref>{{cite book|title=[[Guinness Book of British Hit Singles & Albums|Guinness World Records: British Hit Singles and Albums]] (18th edition)|first=David|last=Roberts|year=2005|isbn=1-904994-00-8|pages=14|publisher=[[HiT Entertainment|Guinness World Records Limited]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/music/3196892.stm |title=New singles formats to save the charts\n|work=[[BBC News]]|date=16 October 2003 |accessdate=21 February 2010}}</ref> Since 2014, the singles chart has been based on both sales and streaming, with the ratio altered in 2017 to 150:1 streams and only three singles by the same artist eligible for the chart.<ref name = \"Rules\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/40405357/official-singles-chart-rules-are-changing-to-help-new-bands-break-through|title=Official Singles Chart rules are changing to help new bands break through|date=26 June 2017|work=Newsbeat|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/official-charts-company-changes-conversion-rate-to-reflect-rise-in-streaming/066932|title=Official Charts Company changes conversion rate to reflect rise in streaming|first=Ben|last=Homewood|date=19 December 2016|work=Music Week|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> From July 2018, video streams from [[YouTube Music]] and [[Spotify]] among others began to be counted for the Official Charts. This list shows singles that peaked in the Top 10 of the [[UK Singles Chart]] during [[2020 in British music|2020]], as well as singles which peaked in [[List of UK top-ten singles in 2019|2019]] but were in the top 10 in 2020. The entry date is when the song appeared in the top 10 for the first time (week ending, as published by the Official Charts Company, which is six days after the chart is announced).\n\nForty singles have been in the top 10 so far this year (as of 23 April 2020, week ending). Eleven singles from 2019 remained in the top 10 for several weeks at the beginning of the year. \"[[All I Want for Christmas is You]]\" by [[Mariah Carey]], \"[[Before You Go (Lewis Capaldi song)|Before You Go]]\" by [[Lewis Capaldi]], \"[[Last Christmas]]\" by [[Wham!]], [[Own It]] by [[Stormzy]] featuring [[Ed Sheeran]] and [[Burna Boy]], \"[[River (Joni Mitchell song)|River]]\" by [[Ellie Goulding]] and \"[[Roxanne (Arizona Zervas song)|Roxanne]]\" by [[Arizona Zervas]] were the singles from 2019 to reach their peak in 2020. Five artists have scored multiple entries in the top ten in 2020. [[Doja Cat]], [[Future (rapper)|Future]] and [[Roddy Ricch]] are among the many artists who have achieved their first top 10 single in 2020.\n\n\"[[Don't Start Now (Dua Lipa song)|Don't Start Now]]\" is currently the single which has spent the most number of consecutive weeks in the top 10 within 2020. The song has spent 16 consecutive weeks in the top 10 in 2020, as well as spending 7 weeks in the top 10 in 2019.\n\nThe first number-one single of the year was \"[[River (Joni Mitchell song)|River]]\" by [[Ellie Goulding]]. Overall, seven different songs have peaked at number-one so far in 2020, with seven unique artists hitting that position. An asterisk (*) in the \"Weeks in Top 10\" column shows that the song is currently in the top 10.\n\n==Background==\n\n===Chart debuts===\nTen artists have achieved their first charting top 10 single in 2020 (as of 23 April 2020, week ending), either as a lead or featured artist.\n\nThe following table (collapsed on desktop site) does not include acts who had previously charted as part of a group and secured their first top 10 solo single.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:55px;\"| Artist\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:55px;\" data-sort-type=\"number\"| Number of top 10s\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| First entry\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:55px;\" data-sort-type=\"number\"| Chart position\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| Other entries\n|-\n|Endor\n|1\n|\"[[Pump It Up!|Pump It Up]]\"\n|8\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Future (rapper)|Future]]\n|1\n|\"[[Life Is Good (song)|Life Is Good]]\"\n|3\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Roddy Ricch]]\n|1\n|\"[[The Box (Roddy Ricch song)|The Box]]\n|2\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|DigDat\n|1\n|\"Ei8ht Mile\"\n|9\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Saint Jhn]]\n|1\n|\"[[Roses (Saint Jhn song)|Roses]]\"\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Doja Cat]]\n|1\n|\"[[Say So (Doja Cat song)|Say So]]\"\n|7\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Tay Keith]]\n|1\n|\"Rain\"\n|3\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Powfu]]\n|1\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:enter\" | \"[[Death Bed]]\"\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:enter\" | 7\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[beabadoobee]]\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|[[Lil Mosey]]\n|1\n|\"[[Blueberry Faygo]]\"\n|9\n|&mdash;\n|-\n|}\n\n===Songs from films===\nOriginal songs from various films entered the top 10 throughout the year. These included \"[[No Time to Die (song)|No Time to Die]]\" (from ''[[No Time to Die]]'').\n\n==Top-ten singles==\n;Key\n{| Class=\"wikitable\"\n!Symbol\n!Meaning\n|-\n|bgcolor=lightblue|\u2021\n|Single peaked in 2019 but still in chart in 2020.\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\" |\u2666\n|Single released in 2020 but peaked in 2021.\n|-\n|<small>(#)</small>\n|Year-end [[2020 in British music#Best-selling singles|top-ten single]] position and rank\n|-\n|'''Entered'''\n|The date that the single first appeared in the chart.\n|-\n|'''Peak'''\n|Highest position that the single reached in the UK Singles Chart.\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Entered <br>(week ending)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Weeks<br>in<br>top<br>10\n! Single\n! Artist\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Peak\n! Peak<br>reached <br>(week ending)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Weeks<br>at<br>peak\n|-\n! colspan=\"9\"|Singles in 2019\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|02|7}}\n| 31\n| align=\"left\"  bgcolor=lightblue|\"[[Someone You Loved]]\" \u2021 {{ref label|Someone|A|a}}{{ref label|Someone|S|s}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Lewis Capaldi]]\n| 1\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|03|7}}\n| 7\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|10|3}}\n| 16\n| align=\"left\"  bgcolor=lightblue|\"[[Dance Monkey]]\" \u2021 {{ref label|Dance|M|m}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Tones and I]]\n| 1\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|10|10}}\n| 11\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|11|7}}\n| 5\n| align=\"left\"  bgcolor=lightblue|\"[[Lose You to Love Me]]\" \u2021 {{ref label|Lose|N|n}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Selena Gomez]]\n| 3\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|11|7}}\n| 1\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|11|14}}\n| 23*\n| align=\"left\"  bgcolor=lightblue|\"[[Don't Start Now (Dua Lipa song)|Don't Start Now]]\" \u2021 {{ref label|Don't|O|o}}\n| align=\"left|[[Dua Lipa]]\n| 2\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|11|14}}\n| 3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|11|28}}\n| 10\n| align=\"left\"  bgcolor=lightblue|\"[[Everything I Wanted]]\" \u2021 {{ref label|Everything|P|p}}{{ref label|Everything|T|t}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Billie Eilish]]\n| 3\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|11|28}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 11\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Roxanne (Arizona Zervas song)|Roxanne]]\" {{ref label|Roxanne|Q|q}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Arizona Zervas]]\n| 4\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|09}}\n| 2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|12|05}}\n| 12\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Before You Go (Lewis Capaldi song)|Before You Go]]\" {{ref label|Before|R|r}}\n| align=\"left|[[Lewis Capaldi]]\n| 1\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|02|06}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 10\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Own It]]\"\n| align=\"left\"|[[Stormzy]] <small>featuring [[Ed Sheeran]] and [[Burna Boy]]</small>\n| 1\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|09}}\n| 3\n|-\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|12|12}}\n| 4\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[All I Want for Christmas Is You]]\" {{ref label|All I Want|B|b}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Mariah Carey]]\n| 2\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|12|19}}\n| 2\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[River (Joni Mitchell song)#Ellie Goulding version|River]]\" {{ref label|River|C|c}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Ellie Goulding]]\n| 1\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 3\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Last Christmas]]\" {{ref label|Last Christmas|D|d}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Wham!]]\n| 3\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\"|Singles in 2020\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|{{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Fairytale of New York]]\" {{ref label|Fairytale of New York|E|e}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[The Pogues]] <small> featuring [[Kirsty MacColl]] </small>\n| 4\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Merry Christmas Everyone]]\" {{ref label|Merry Christmas Everyone|F|f}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Shakin' Stevens]]\n| 6\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Do They Know It's Christmas?]]\" {{ref label|Band Aid|G|g}}{{ref label|Do They Know It's Christmas|H|h}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Band Aid (band)|Band Aid]]\n| 7\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Step into Christmas]]\" {{ref label|Elton John|I|i}}\n| align=\"left\"|[[Elton John]]\n| 8\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[Happy Xmas (War is Over)#Other versions|Happy Xmas (War is Over)]]\"\n| align=\"left\"|[[John Legend]]\n| 9\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|01|02}}\n| 1\n|-\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|\"[[I Wish It Could Be Christmas Eve